' bug-251 regression: two imported binding packages declare a `LINK` block with
' the SAME alias (`fooLink`) and the SAME function name (`raw`), each bound to a
' DIFFERENT native symbol. The link-function merge used to de-duplicate on the
' package-internal `(alias, name)` in a project-global namespace, dropping the
' second package's thunk and silently routing its calls to the first package's
' library/symbol. Each package's wrapper must call ITS OWN symbol.
'
' collidera::op() = 7 iff A's `sqlite3_strglob` answered; colliderb::op() = 3 iff
' B's `sqlite3_stricmp` answered. Correct routing => 7*10 + 3 = 73. Any misroute
' (either thunk dropped) makes at least one op() return 0, so the exit code is
' never 73 under the bug.
IMPORT collidera
IMPORT colliderb

FUNC main() AS Integer
  LET a AS Integer = collidera::op()
  LET b AS Integer = colliderb::op()
  RETURN a * 10 + b
END FUNC
